=== PRM Scoring: PR #6266 ===
Date: 2026-04-17
Technique: PRM (Process Reward Model)

PR Title: [antig] fix: remove anchor in skeptic verdict regex to capture bold formatting
PR Link: https://github.com/jleechanorg/worldarchitect.ai/pull/6266

=== PRM Step-by-Step Reasoning ===

Step 1: Understand the Bug
- Original grep pattern: grep -i "^[[:space:]]*VERDICT:" (anchored to line start)
- Problem: If verdict has **bold** markers on the same line as VERDICT:, the anchor fails
- Example failure: "**VERDICT: LGTM**" won't match due to ** prefix

Step 2: Analyze the Fix
- Removed ^ anchor: grep -i "VERDICT:" now matches anywhere in the text
- Added ** stripping: sed -e 's/^\*\*//' -e 's/\*\*$//' removes bold markers
- Preserves whitespace stripping: sed 's/^[[:space:]]*//'

Step 3: Score Each Rubric Dimension

**Naming (15%)**
- VERDICT_LINE: Standard shell convention, clear intent
- MERGE_COMMENT_FILE: Descriptive, follows naming patterns
- Score: 15/20

**Error Handling (20%)**
- Has fallback: || echo "VERDICT: UNKNOWN"
- Graceful degradation when grep finds nothing
- Score: 16/20

**Type Safety (20%)**
- Shell scripts are inherently untyped
- Variables are strings only
- Score: 12/20 (shell baseline)

**Architecture (20%)**
- Clean single-line fix
- No architectural changes
- Minimal blast radius
- Score: 16/20

**Test Coverage (15%)**
- No test changes visible in diff
- Shell script testing would require mocking environment
- Score: 8/20

**Documentation (10%)**
- Comment explains block prefix check purpose
- Clear context for the fix
- Score: 14/20

=== Final Score ===
Total: 15+16+12+16+8+14 = 81/100

